div.p:
I cannot but much wonder indeed at what you tell us concerning the Earle of Ormond;
               Civilis. I doe remember him here in England under the care of Abbot Archbiſhop of Canterbury, and (for what I could diſcerne in his younger yeers) there appeared in him the hopes of better performances; and truly sir, I will not diſſemble with you, I have heard from many that are come from Dublin, and are ſtill in this City, and on whom the Parliament has beſtowed ſome other marks of

of their favour, beſides admitting of them to reſide here; that he has carried himſelfe from the beginning with all reſpect and good conſcience to the Engliſh, and as one firmly rooted and reſolved in the proteſtant Religion.
